=== Etymology 2 ===
Old English ''[[tidan|tīdan]]'' ‘to happen’.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|tid|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To cause to float with the tide; to drive or carry with the tide or stream.
#:They are tided down the stream. &mdash; [[Feltham?]]
# {{cattag|intransitive|obsolete}} To betide; to happen.
#:What should us tide of this new law? &mdash; [[Geoffrey Chaucer]]
# {{intransitive}} To pour a tide or flood.
# {{cattag|nautical}} To work into or out of a river or harbor by drifting with the tide and anchoring when it becomes adverse.

